    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a high-upside slate today, headlined by **Yordan Alvarez** (81.999) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (79.310). **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and an elite .393 xwOBA, positioning him as our most reliable run producer against Baz. Meanwhile, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is our primary source of stolen base equity today; despite an unfavorable park, he draws a favorable matchup against Buehler (5.19 xERA) and faces a catcher with slow delivery mechanics, boosting his efficiency score significantly as he hunts for swipes. **Trea Turner** (76.320) and **Kyle Schwarber** (73.947) also project as elite starts, leveraging the favorable matchup against Mahle to anchor the top of our lineup.\n\nEfficiency optimization necessitated tough calls at the margins, specifically regarding **Luke Raley** (43.900) and **Caleb Durbin** (47.641). While **Caleb Durbin** maintains value due to his positional utility, his #9 spot in the order hampered his raw output. **Colt Keith** was our most notable bench exclusion; although he technically profiles well against P\u00e9rez, the decision to leave him out reflects the priority on the higher-ceiling platoon advantages presented by **Dillon Dingler** (63.898) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (59.512). The lineup remains aggressive, though we are tracking **Trea Turner** closely, as any late-breaking wind reports at the stadium could neutralize the expected production against Mahle. With **Christian Yelich** sidelined and **Zac Veen** currently stashed in the minors, our active depth must capitalize on these exploitable xERA targets to maintain our pace in the 5x5 standings.",
